    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A natural organic colorant extracted from the roots of any of several species of the genus Rubia, having a reddish color. Madder has been used as a colorant for dyeing textiles since ancient times in India, Persia, and Egypt. It has been largely replaced as a dye and a pigment by synthetic alizarin. Used for dye and lake pigment preparation.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
